From: =?UTF-8?q?Micha=C5=82=20G=C3=B3rny?= <mgorny@quansight.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 14:24:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] Make `test_aot` importable without a GPU backend
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fix a `NameError` when the test file is being imported without GPU
available:

```
_____________ ERROR collecting python/test/unit/tools/test_aot.py ______________
python/test/unit/tools/test_aot.py:118: in <module>
    test_utils_src += """
E   NameError: name 'test_utils_src' is not defined
```

This happens because a0e769fc26e4adefca6522598ab3969b089be45c introduced
logic that defines different initial values for global-scope
`test_utils_src` variable depending on whether CUDA or HIP is available.
However, when neither of these are available, the variable is not
declared at all and the code trying to append to it subsequently fails.

Instead, fill the value with a plain `#error` if no backend is found.
The relevant tests will still fail but the file will be importable
again, which we need for minimal conda-forge testing.

Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@quansight.com>
---
 python/test/unit/tools/test_aot.py | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/python/test/unit/tools/test_aot.py b/python/test/unit/tools/test_aot.py
index 5cc38b16ae..05889f834f 100644
--- a/python/test/unit/tools/test_aot.py
+++ b/python/test/unit/tools/test_aot.py
@@ -114,6 +114,10 @@ elif is_hip():
 #define __HIP_PLATFORM_AMD__
 #include <hip/hip_runtime.h>
 """
+else:
+    test_utils_src = """
+#error "No GPU backend available"
+"""
 
 test_utils_src += """
 #include <stdio.h>
